<title type="html"><![CDATA[Famicom 3D System]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=974&amp;p=57553#p57553"><![CDATA[
<div class="quotetitle">CKY-2K/Clay Man wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />3-D Battles of World Runner, The (U)<br /><br />I just put that on Pocketnes last night and realized it has a 3D red/blue depth mode.<br /></div><br /><br />That's a different method of making a 3-D game than the 3-D system uses. The 3-D goggles for the Famicom use a flickering doubled image, but it isn’t Red/Blue. It’s closer to the way a stereoscope works, and the shutters open and close rapidly to provide a single image to your eyes.<br /><br />There are only a handful of games for the 3-D system, and there is no way to emulate them purely in software, as they require the shuttering system to function.<br /><br />The Red/Blue games work flawlessly with any Red/Blue 3-D glasses. I have a prescription set for just that reason. <img src="http://forums.nesdev.com/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />-Xious<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4070">Xious</a> — Fri Mar 05, 2010 9:01 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
