(I'm sorry I don't know the Japanese language)<br /><br />This 3D system you're talking about, if I'm right it seems to be 2 small screens, alternating between on and off status every frame ? It can be enabled by pressing the select key in those games you mentioned (eg. "Highway Star").<br /><br />One way I can think of to make this effect emulatable is quite easy: output 2 images next to eachother (one showing odd frames, the other showing even frames, and let the user cross their eyes to create a 3D view, like this: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.vision3d.com/sgphotoc.html">http://www.vision3d.com/sgphotoc.html</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=115">hap</a> — Sun Jan 29, 2006 11:42 am</p><hr />
